Q: Can the House Judiciary Committee only approve one of the two articles of impeachment? A: Yes, then only the article that House Judiciary Committee approves will go to the House floor to be voted on by the whole House of Representatives. 
Q: If President Trump is impeached, can he still run for a second term? A: Yes. If Trump is formally impeached and NOT removed from office by the Senate, he can run for a second term. 
Q: If the House Judiciary Committee approves the articles of impeachment, when will the whole House vote on them?
